    <example xml:id="ex_vvfderiv3">
      <title>Finding tangent lines to curves</title>
      <statement>
        <p>Find the equations of the lines tangent to <m>\vec r(t) = \la t^3,t^2\ra</m> at <m>t=-1</m> and <m>t=0</m>.</p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>We find that <m>\vrp(t) = \la 3t^2,2t\ra</m>. At <m>t=-1</m>, we have
          <me>
            \vec r(-1) = \la -1,1\ra \text{ and }  \vrp(-1) = \la 3,-2\ra,
          </me>
          so the equation of the line tangent to the graph of <m>\vec r(t)</m> at <m>t=-1</m> is
          <me>
            \ell(t) = \la -1,1\ra + t\la 3,-2\ra.
          </me>
        </p>

        <p>This line is graphed with <m>\vec r(t)</m> in <xref ref="fig_vvfderiv3">Figure</xref>.</p>

